across india, buses are the second most popular way of travelling across states and the only cheap way of reaching many places not on the rail network (eg. dharamsala). every state has its own public bus service, usually named "x road transport corporation" (or xrtc) or "x state transport corporation" (or xstc) which primarily connects intra-state routes, but will also have services to neighbouring states. there are usually multiple classes of buses. the ordinary buses (called differently in different states, e.g. "service bus") are extremely crowded with even standing room rarely available (unless you're among the first on board) as 